<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-17T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-17T08:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-17T09:00:00-04:00">February 17, 1936—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>15. Revolutionary movement broke out early this morning. It is rumored
                            that garrison at Paraguari and several local forces, including military
                            school and aviation, have revolted and are said to be marching on
                            Asunción. There is intermittent firing in the center of the city.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>